  
** Fantastic opportunity for an experienced Mechanical & Piping Engineer to be part of a growing & exciting team from their Brisbane site working for a well know mining organisation within their capital projects. **   
** **   

  * ** Permanent role with an attractive annual salary + great additional benefits **
  * ** PMO **
  * ** Tier 1 Gold mining producer **
  * ** Fulltime with an immediate start **
** **   
** The role : **   
The Mechanical and Piping Engineer is responsible for ensuring the quality of
civil, structural and geotechnical engineering in capital projects. This
extends to ensuring project surveying is adequate for correct project
execution. The position is responsible for adhering to site and international
standards and specifications. They position is to carry out assigned work
under the guidance of the Engineering Superintendent, following discipline
plans, project schedules, budgets, design basis and engineering standards.
They also undertake engineering activities such as detailed design,
specification writing and checking of drawings on specific projects and review
submissions from external consultants.  
  
** **   

  * Highlights to the Engineering Superintendent difficulties in complying with the above requirements. 
  * Brings to the notice of the Engineering Superintendent any changes in scope. 
  * Maintains an awareness of other disciplines and advises the Engineering Superintendent of coordination problems. 
  * Produces design calculations reports for submittal for verification and certification as required. 
  * Coordinates with disciplines to ensure timely verification of designs. 
  * Managing design sub-consultants (administration of subcontract purchasing is responsibility of the Project Manager). 
  * Stakeholder requirement specification (SRS). 
  * Participate in Project Morning Run meetings, 3 per weey, and ensure all discipline inputs are included where required. 
  * Participate in P&E Interface and P&E Construction meetings, held weekly, and ensure all discipline requirements are understood by all participants. 
  * Ensure all discipline Project Controls Dashboard inputs are entered in a timely manner Development and review of project charters and work scope s, complete with options. 
  * Design change management, including processing PCR’s. 
  * Assist with key equipment specifications and selection. 
  * Sign off at design completion for design handover. 
  * Assist with technical feasibility studies. 
  * Engineering, detailed design, specification writing, and checking of drawings at the different project gates for in-house works . 
  * Participate in deliverability/ constructability assessment and technical feasibility reviews (HAZARD Study #2, #3) . 
  * Run Safety in Design workshops and implement actions. 
  * Consider inputs and feedback from Construction Supplier . 
  * Consider inputs and feedback from Operations team. 
  * Ensures that design calculations and all engineering related correspondence are collected, indexed and properly filed. 
  * Engineering statutory compliance auditing and solution. 
  * Review of designs provided by the Engineering Suppliers. 
  * Engineering suppliers technical due diligence 
  * Facilitate design gates approvals. 
  * Quality management of engineering deliverables. 
  * Attendance to Contractor’s Safety in Design workshops, ensure records of same are saved. 
  * Establish uniform engineering and technical criteria, methods, processes and practices. 
  * Issue Construction Handover package to Construction Supplier 
  * ** Person Specification **   
** Qualifications (essential and desirable): **   

  * Tertiary qualification in an Engineering. 
** Behavioural Competencies ** _ (4-5 personal skills that are critical for success; reference Newcrest Competency Framework) _   

  * Demonstrates personal responsibility for own health and safety whilst setting clear expectations of relevant legal obligations, safe workplace practices and HSE operating practices for others, holding them accountable for their actions. 
  * Assimilates and applies new job-related knowledge and skills received through feedback, exposure, coaching and formal training. 
  * Embodies and exemplifies Newmont’s vision and values. 
  * Stays focused and composed in stressful situations. 
  * Demonstrates the ability to work constructively with diverse groups and cultures. 
** Technical Capabilities ** _ (4-5 technical skills including systems / technology that are critical for success) _   

    * Competence in; 
      * Engineering Design Software, 
      * Computer proficiency in MS Office (intermediate), 
      * Spreadsheet and database applications (intermediate). 
    * Capacity to learn; 
      * New software (general), 
      * To read native AutoCAD drawings. 
      * To read native project specific 2D/3D drafting packages (general). 
    * ** Required Knowledge and Experience (essential and desirable): **   
Essential  

